Many believe that with the government constantly printing money, the US dollar could be devalued very soon, which many believe could lead to the one world currency referred to in prophecy. You've also got Russia, China, Iran, Venezuela, and other nations demanding that the world move away from the US Dollar as the worlds trading currency - which would drop the dollar overnight like the peso once did. If the world switches to a 'common' currency, it will have to move to something backing that currencies value, and in order to be equitable to all nations it will likely mean a return to the gold standard of some sort. You may have heard that Russia and China have been quietly buying up all the gold they can get without disturbing the markets, and that Germany wants all their gold moved from the USA over to its own banks. What does all this mean for our economy? The US dollar could become as wall paper, gold would be king, and silver, being the poor mans gold, would follow right along with it. In other words, silver is an affordable commodity for you and I that has no where to go but up. Keep in mind also that while 95% of all the gold ever mined is still in use, silver is a disposable or consumable metal meaning it is generally not recycled, there are more uses for silver than there is for gold, and when our bottom starts to fall out from beneath us, everybody and their brother who cannot afford gold will be looking to buy silver - which will skyrocket the price/value. And lastly, in a time of crisis, silver is also a good currency alternative that will always have value.

title: For Sale:  RUSSIAN SVT-40 SEMI AUTO 7.62X54R MILITARY SURPLUS RIFLE, 10rd MAGAZINE
postcontent:
Military Surplus RUSSIAN SVT-40 RIFLE - 7.62x54r caliber semi-automatic rifle that are no longer imported. 10 round magazine. The Samozaryadnaya Vintovka Tokareva (SVT-40) was designed by Soviet Arms Designer Fedor Tokarev. It was manufactured between 1941 and 1945. The SVT-40 is an improved and simplified rifle design over the SVT-38. 
During WWII SVT-40 rifles were highly prized captures by both German and Finnish troops. Many pictures in books of German troops on the eastern front carrying the SVT-40. 
The biggest issue with the SVT 40 is the ejection of the spent casing due to improper gas cartridge adjustment and improper powder loads. DO NOT use any loads over 150 grain as this will destroy the gas chamber. Overall condition is rated as fair to good for an old surplus military rifle that will never be imported again into the USA. 10rd magazine is an aftermarket so not all original. Great for shooting , collecting or the one that got away! Serious Inquiries Only Please!!! "Pay us a visit--there's always something new and interesting in the shop!"

title: For Sale:  Diana RWS 54 Air King .177 Cal. with Scope and Case
postcontent:
A totally recoilless, spring piston airgun seemed little more than a dream before the recent appearance of the Model 54. In order to realize this goal the engineers spent years experimenting with different systems until they created this mechanical marvel. Simple but durable, the 54 uses a floating action riding on rails to achieve a totally recoiless system that stands up to the pounding of our 1100 fps system. Not only does this arrangement prevent transmission of felt recoil to the shooter, it also permits the rifle to excel in the accuracy department. When the rifle is fired, the action moves back lightly within the stock, absorbing the recoil, and permitting the pellet to exit the barrel before any of the spring vibration affects its travel. This system dramatically improves the accuracy potential of this magnum air rifle, making it a first class choice for either long range pest control or the precise demands of field target shooting. This side lever cocking magnum rifle's other features include adjustable trigger, adjustable rear sight, scope rail, Monte Carlo stock with cheek piece and checkering, and an automatic safety.
Sells on-line for $595.00 without the scope and case.
On a scale of 1-10 (10 being excellent) this would be an 8.
Call REDACTED with any questions
